<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-08-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-08-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 a 1/539b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-03T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>95. This morning the Democratic leader in the Senate (Robinson) called on
                            me. I discussed with him the entire situation at Geneva. Thoroughly
                            approving our course, he says he will support it. If speeches are made,
                            he said we should state our position fully and frankly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>